rate complex systems that link scientific and cultural practices: graphic medicine, landscape architecture, and bioArt. Challenging reductive understandings of epigenetics, Squier boldly reclaims the broader significance of the epigenetic landscape as a figure at the nexus of art, design, and science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aArt and science. 0aEpigeneticsxPhilosophy. 0aEpigeneticsxSocial aspects. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Genetics & Genomics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311069634940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822372608423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822372608/original  a978-3-11-069634-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles